        <dc:type>InWork</dc:type>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">for an inductive two-terminal element with terminals A and B, quotient of the linked flux Ψ between the terminals by the electric current i in the element L = Ψ/i where the sign of the linked flux is determined by taking the voltage, in the time integral defining it, as the difference of the electric potentials at terminals at A and B, and where the current is taken as positive if its direction is from A to B and negative if its direction is from B to A</rdfs:comment>
